	   <tr><td colspan=2>LOL..Me too.&nbsp;&nbsp;Actually knocked myself unconscious!  When Allure was new to me I always welcomed a passing plant witch throwing regen on me.  It meant I could have the equiv' of clarity going with no pain.  Yes I can heal myself, but it isn't free.  Straight damage DOT's are much more mana-damage efficient.  At certain levels having innate regen would be a nice plus.  I found hp buffs also worked to offset the cost of &quot;necro-clarity&quot;.  Hmm.. that means +hp items would help as well... and they do.<br>As for race diff's in general, I felt a bit underpowered by my low Int early in life, so I bought inexpensive +mana items to get me into the 20's, when I could afford, and make good use of +Int.  A few of the items were quite usable to 30th.  Fact is all racial differences will blur in importance as we reach higher levels and item buff our character to fit our favorite style of play.<br><br>BTW, lets not forget the importance of DEX to any caster who likes to solo.<br>--THE human necromancer<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Saaron Shadowraaithe<br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
